SportsTeamSeason.description: A season for a particular sports team (as opposed to the season for the entire league that the team is in)

StatedResolution.label: Stated Resolution
StatedResolution.description: A Resolution describes a formal statement adopted by a meeting or convention.

Station.label: station
Station.description: Public transport station (eg. railway station, metro station, bus station).

StillImage.label: still image
StillImage.description: A visual document that is not intended to be animated; equivalent to http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/StillImage

StormSurge.label: storm surge
StormSurge.description: Een stormvloed is de grootschalige overstroming van een kustgebied onder invloed van de op elkaar inwerkende krachten van wind, getij en water

Stream.label: stream
Stream.description: a flowing body of water with a current, confined within a bed and stream banks

Street.label: street
Street.description: A Street is different from a Road in as far as the infrastructure aspect is much less important here. A Street is a social and architectural ensemble much more than the connection between two geographic points.

SubMunicipality.label: borough
SubMunicipality.description: An administrative body governing a territorial unity on the lowest level, administering part of a municipality

SupremeCourtOfTheUnitedStatesCase.label: Supreme Court of the United States case

Swimmer.label: swimmer
Swimmer.description: a trained athlete who participates in swimming meets

Synagogue.label: synagogue
Synagogue.description: A synagogue, sometimes spelt synagog, is a Jewish or Samaritan house of prayer.

SystemOfLaw.label: System of law
SystemOfLaw.description: a system of legislation, either national or international

Taxon.label: taxonomic group
Taxon.description: a category within a classification system for Species

TeamMember.label: Team member
TeamMember.description: A member of an athletic team.

TeamSport.label: team sport
TeamSport.description: A team sport is commonly defined as a sport that is being played by competing teams

TelevisionDirector.label: Television director
TelevisionDirector.description: a person who directs the activities involved in making a television program.

TelevisionEpisode.label: television episode
TelevisionEpisode.description: A television episode is a part of serial television program.

TelevisionStation.label: television station
TelevisionStation.description: A television station has usually one line up. For instance the television station WABC-TV (or ABC 7, Channel 7). Not to be confused with the broadcasting network ABC, which has many television stations.

TennisLeague.label: tennis league
TennisLeague.description: A group of sports teams or person that compete against each other in tennis.

Territory.label: territory
Territory.description: A territory may refer to a country subdivision, a non-sovereign geographic region.

Theatre.label: theatre
Theatre.description: A theater or theatre (also a playhouse) is a structure where theatrical works or plays are performed or other performances such as musical concerts may be produced.

TheatreDirector.label: Theatre director
TheatreDirector.description: A director in the theatre field who oversees and orchestrates the mounting of a theatre production.

TheologicalConcept.label: Theological concept
TheologicalConcept.description: Theological concepts, e.g. The apocalypse, Trinty, Stoicism

Tower.label: tower
Tower.description: A Tower is a kind of structure (not necessarily a building) that is higher than the rest

Town.label: town
Town.description: a settlement ranging from a few hundred to several thousand (occasionally hundreds of thousands). The precise meaning varies between countries and is not always a matter of legal definition. Usually, a town is thought of as larger than a village but smaller than a city, though there are exceptions to this rule.

TrackList.label: track list
TrackList.description: A list of music tracks, like on a CD

TradeUnion.label: trade union
TradeUnion.description: A trade union or labor union is an organization of workers who have banded together to achieve common goals such as better working conditions.

Treadmill.label: Treadmill
Treadmill.description: A mill driven by the tractive power of horses, donkeys or even people

Tunnel.label: tunnel
Tunnel.description: A tunnel may be for foot or vehicular road traffic, for rail traffic, or for a canal. Some tunnels are aqueducts to supply water for consumption or for hydroelectric stations or are sewers (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tunnel).

Type.label: type
Type.description: a category within a classification system

UndergroundJournal.label: underground journal
UndergroundJournal.description: An underground journal is, although over time there have always been publications forbidden by law, a phenomenon typical of countries occupied by the Germans during the Second World War. The writing in the underground press aims at stiffening a spirit of resistance against Nazi occupation. The distribution of underground journals had to be very secretive and was, therefore, very much dependant on illegal distribution circuits and the hazards of persecution by the occupant.

UnitOfWork.label: unit of work
UnitOfWork.description: This class is meant to convey the notion of an amount work to be done. It is different from Activity in that it has a definite end and is being measured.

Valley.label: valley
Valley.description: a depression with predominant extent in one direction

VideoGame.label: video game
VideoGame.description: A video game is an electronic game that involves interaction with a user interface to generate visual feedback on a video device.

VideogamesLeague.label: videogames league
VideogamesLeague.description: A group of sports teams or person that compete against each other in videogames.

Village.label: village
Village.description: a clustered human settlement or community, usually smaller a town

Volcano.label: volcano
Volcano.description: A volcano is currently subclass of naturalplace, but it might also be considered a mountain.

VolleyballLeague.label: volleyball league
VolleyballLeague.description: A group of sports teams that compete against each other in volleyball.

WaterTower.label: Water tower
WaterTower.description: a construction designed to store larger quantities of water at a place of some elevation in order to keep pressure on the water provision system

Watermill.label: Watermill
Watermill.description: A watermill is a structure that uses a water wheel or turbine to drive a mechanical process such as flour, lumber or textile production, or metal shaping (rolling, grinding or wire drawing)

WindMotor.label: Wind motor
WindMotor.description: A wind-driven turbine that adapts itself to wind direction and to wind-force. Is considered to be a class in its own, despite the wind as common factor with Windmill.

Windmill.label: Windmill
Windmill.description: A windmill is a machine that converts the energy of wind into rotational energy by means of vanes called sails

WorldHeritageSite.label: World Heritage Site
WorldHeritageSite.description: A UNESCO World Heritage Site is a site (such as a forest, mountain, lake, desert, monument, building, complex, or city) that is on the list that is maintained by the international World Heritage Programme administered by the UNESCO World Heritage Committee, composed of 21 state parties which are elected by their General Assembly for a four-year term. A World Heritage Site is a place of either cultural or physical significance.

WrittenWork.label: written work
WrittenWork.description: Written work is any text written to read it (e.g.: books, newspaper, articles)

abstentions.label: abstentions
abstentions.description: Number of abstentions from the vote

academicDiscipline.label: academic discipline
academicDiscipline.description: An academic discipline, or field of study, is a branch of knowledge that is taught and researched at the college or university level. Disciplines are defined (in part), and recognized by the academic journals in which research is published, and the learned societies and academic departments or faculties to which their practitioners belong.

activeYears.label: active years
activeYears.description: Also called "floruit". Use this if the active years are in one field that can't be split. Else use activeYearsStartYear and activeYearsEndYear

address.label: address
address.description: Address of something as literal. Usually Building, but we also use it for the address of a Region's or Settlement's government

addressInRoad.label: address in road
addressInRoad.description: A building, organisation or other thing that is located in the road.

adjacentSettlement.label: adjacent settlement of a switzerland settlement

administrativeHeadCity.label: head city
administrativeHeadCity.description: city where stand the administrative power

ageRange.label: age range
ageRange.description: Age range of students admitted in a School, MilitaryUnit, etc

agencyStationCode.label: agency station code
agencyStationCode.description: Agency station code (used on tickets/reservations, etc.).

allegiance.label: allegiance
allegiance.description: The country or other power the person served. Multiple countries may be indicated together with the corresponding dates. This field should not be used to indicate a particular service branch, which is better indicated by the branch field.

alpsGroup.label: Alps group
alpsGroup.description: the Alps group to which the mountain belongs, according to the SOIUSA classification

alpsMainPart.label: Alps main part
alpsMainPart.description: the Alps main part to which the mountain belongs, according to the SOIUSA classification

alpsMajorSector.label: Alps major sector
alpsMajorSector.description: the Alps major sector to which the mountain belongs, according to the SOIUSA classification

alpsSection.label: Alps section
alpsSection.description: the Alps section to which the mountain belongs, according to the SOIUSA classification

alpsSoiusaCode.label: Alps SOIUSA code
alpsSoiusaCode.description: the Alps SOIUSA code corresponding to the mountain, according to the SOIUSA classification

alpsSubgroup.label: Alps subgroup
alpsSubgroup.description: the Alps subgroup to which the mountain belongs, according to the SOIUSA classification

alpsSubsection.label: Alps subsection
alpsSubsection.description: the Alps subsection to which the mountain belongs, according to the SOIUSA classification

alpsSupergroup.label: Alps supergroup
alpsSupergroup.description: the Alps supergroup to which the mountain belongs, according to the SOIUSA classification

alternativeName.label: alternative name
alternativeName.description: Alternative naming of anything not being a Person (for which case foaf:nick should be used).

alternativeTitle.label: alternative title
alternativeTitle.description: The alternative title attributed to a work

anthem.label: anthem
anthem.description: Official song (anthem) of a PopulatedPlace, SportsTeam, School or other

approvedByLowerParliament.label: date of approval by lower parliament
approvedByLowerParliament.description: Date of approval by lower parliament (House of Commons, Chambre des Députés, Bundestag, Tweede Kamer etc.).

approvedByUpperParliament.label: date of approval by upper parliament
approvedByUpperParliament.description: Date of approval by upper parliament (House of Lords, Sénat, Eerste Kamer etc.).

area.label: area (m2)
area.description: The area of the thing in square meters.

areaCode.label: area code
areaCode.description: Area code for telephone numbers. Use this not phonePrefix

artPatron.label: patron (art)
artPatron.description: An influential, wealthy person who supported an artist, craftsman, a scholar or a noble.. See also

artist.label: performer
artist.description: The performer or creator of the musical work.

asWikiText.label: Contains a WikiText representation of this thing

ascent.label: ascent
ascent.description: Ascent of a celestial body, aircraft, etc. For person who ascended a mountain, use firstAscent

assets.label: assets ($)
assets.description: Assets and liabilities are part of a companis balance sheet. In financial accounting, assets are economic resources. Anything tangible or intangible that is capable of being owned or controlled to produce value and that is held to have positive economic value is considered an asset.

atPage.label: page number
atPage.description: Page # where the referenced resource is to be found in the source document

atRowNumber.label: row number
atRowNumber.description: Row # where the referenced resource is to be found in the source file

atomicNumber.label: atomic number
atomicNumber.description: the ratio of the average mass of atoms of an element (from a single given sample or source) to 1⁄12 of the mass of an atom of carbon-12

authorityTitle.label: authority title of a romanian settlement

availableSmartCard.label: available smart card
availableSmartCard.description: Smartcard for fare payment system for public transit systems that are or will be available at the station.

averageDepth.label: average depth (μ)
averageDepth.description: Source of the value can be declare by .

averageSpeed.label: average speed (kmh)
averageSpeed.description: The average speed of a thing.

award.label: award
award.description: Award won by a Person, Musical or other Work, RaceHorse, Building, etc

awardName.label: awardName
awardName.description: Award a person has received (literal). Compare to award (ObjectProperty)

awayColourHexCode.label: colour hex code of away jersey or its parts
awayColourHexCode.description: A colour represented by its hex code (e.g.: #FF0000 or #40E0D0).

bibsysId.label: BIBSYS Id
bibsysId.description: BIBSYS is a supplier of library and information systems for all Norwegian university Libraries, the National Library of Norway, college libraries, and a number of research libraries and institutions.

bioavailability.label: Bioavailability
bioavailability.description: "The rate and extent to which the active ingredient or active moiety is absorbed from a drug product and becomes available at the site of action. For drug products that are not intended to be absorbed into the bloodstream, bioavailability may be assessed by measurements intended to reflect the rate and extent to which the active ingredient or active moiety becomes available at the site of action (21CFR320.1)."

bishopric.label: bishopric
bishopric.description: A bishopric (diocese or episcopal see) is a district under the supervision of a bishop. It is divided into parishes. Compare with eparchy

blazon.label: blazon
blazon.description: Coat of arms (heraldic image) or emblem

bnfId.label: BNF Id
bnfId.description: Authority data of people listed in the general catalogue of the National Library of France

bpnId.label: BPN Id
bpnId.description: Dutch project with material for 40,000 digitized biographies, including former colonies of the Netherlands.

bridgeCarries.label: bridge carries
bridgeCarries.description: Type of vehicles the bridge carries.

broadcastNetwork.label: broadcast network
broadcastNetwork.description: The parent broadcast network to which the broadcaster belongs.

buildingEndDate.label: building end date
buildingEndDate.description: Building end date of an ArchitecturalStructure, man-made Lake, etc. For older structures this can be just a year or century, for newer structures an exact date is preferred

buildingStartDate.label: building start date
buildingStartDate.description: Building start date of an ArchitecturalStructure, man-made Lake, etc. For older structures this can be just a year or century, for newer structures an exact date is preferred

buildingType.label: buildingType
buildingType.description: Type is too general. We should be able to distinguish types of music from types of architecture

bustWaistHipSize.label: bust-waist-hip Size
bustWaistHipSize.description: Use this property if all 3 sizes are given together (DBpedia cannot currently extract 3 Lengths out of a field). Otherwise use separate fields bustSize, waistSize, hipSize

callSign.label: call sign
callSign.description: A call sign is not the name of a broadcaster! In broadcasting and radio communications, a call sign (also known as a call name or call letters, or abbreviated as a call) is a unique designation for a transmitting station.

capacity.label: capacity
capacity.description: Number of people who can be served by a Train or other service; or participate in a SoccerClub, CricketTeam, etc

carbohydrate.label: carbohydrate (g)
carbohydrate.description: Amount of carbohydrates per servingSize of a Food

careerStation.description: this property links to a step in the career of a person, e.g. a soccer player, holding information on the time span, matches and goals he or she achieved at a club.

casNumber.label: CAS number
casNumber.description: Chemical Abstracts Service number. Applicable to ChemicalCompound or Biomolecule (eg Protein)

casualties.label: casualties
casualties.description: Number of casualties of a MilitaryConflict or natural disaster such as an Earthquake

ceiling.label: ceiling
ceiling.description: Maximum distance to the earth surface, to be expressed in kilometers

centuryBreaks.label: century breaks
centuryBreaks.description: number of breaks with 100 points and more

chEBI.label: ChEBI
chEBI.description: A unique identifier for the drug in the Chemical Entities of Biological Interest (ChEBI) ontology

chain.label: chain
chain.description: The chain of Hotels this instance is associated with.

championInDouble.label: champion in double
championInDouble.description: winner of a competition in the double session (as in tennis)

championInDoubleFemale.label: champion in double female
championInDoubleFemale.description: winner of a competition in the female double session (as in tennis)

championInDoubleMale.label: champion in double male
championInDoubleMale.description: winner of a competition in the male double session (as in tennis)

championInMixedDouble.label: champion in mixed double
championInMixedDouble.description: winner of a competition in the mixed double session (as in tennis)

championInSingle.label: champion in single
championInSingle.description: winner of a competition in the single session, to distinguish from the double session (as in tennis)

championInSingleFemale.label: champion in single female
championInSingleFemale.description: winner of a competition in the single female session, to distinguish from the double session (as in tennis)

championInSingleMale.label: champion in single male
championInSingleMale.description: winner of a competition in the single male session, to distinguish from the double session (as in tennis)

characterInPlay.label: character in play
characterInPlay.description: Name of a character in play.

chorusCharacterInPlay.label: chorus character in play
chorusCharacterInPlay.description: The name of the (Greek) chorus character in play.

cites.label: cites
cites.description: A document cited by this work. Like OntologyProperty:dct:references, but as a datatype property.

cityRank.label: city rank
cityRank.description: Place of the building in the list of the highest buildings in the city

classis.label: classis
classis.description: the living thing class (from the Latin "classis"), according to the biological taxonomy

cmykCoordinateBlack.label: black coordinate in the CMYK space

cmykCoordinateCyanic.label: cyanic coordinate in the CMYK space

cmykCoordinateMagenta.label: magenta coordinate in the CMYK space

cmykCoordinateYellow.label: yellow coordinate in the CMYK space

coatOfArms.label: coat of arms image
coatOfArms.description: image of the coat of arms (heraldic symbol)

codeBook.label: code book
codeBook.description: code book or statute book referred to in this legal case

codeLandRegistry.label: code land registry
codeLandRegistry.description: Land Registry code designating a parcel of land

codeMemorial.label: memorial ID number
codeMemorial.description: Identifier for monuments of the Memorial type

codeMunicipalMonument.label: monument code (municipal)
codeMunicipalMonument.description: Code assigned to (Dutch) monuments at the municipal level, deemed to be of local value

codeNationalMonument.label: monument code (national)
codeNationalMonument.description: Code assigned to (Dutch) monuments at the national level, deemed to be of national value

codeProvincialMonument.label: monument code (provinciall)
codeProvincialMonument.description: Code assigned to (Dutch) monuments at the provincial level, mostly for monuments in the countryside, or for waterworks

coden.label: CODEN
coden.description: CODEN is a six character, alphanumeric bibliographic code, that provides concise, unique and unambiguous identification of the titles of serials and non-serial publications from all subject areas.

colleague.label: colleague
colleague.description: Colleague of a Person or OfficeHolder (not PersonFunction nor CareerStation). Sub-properties include: president, vicePresident, chancellor, viceChancellor, governor, lieutenant. Points to a Person who may have a general "position" (resource) or "title" (literal).

colour.label: colour
colour.description: A colour represented by its entity.

colourHexCode.label: colour hex code
colourHexCode.description: A colour represented by its hex code (e.g.: #FF0000 or #40E0D0).

colourName.label: colour name
colourName.description: A colour represented by a string holding its name (e.g.: red or green).

committeeInLegislature.label: committee in legislature
committeeInLegislature.description: Committee in the legislature (eg.: Committee on Economic and Monetary Affairs of the European Parliament).

commonName.label: common name
commonName.description: The common name of an entity. Frequently, foaf:name is used for all of the different names of a person; this property just defines the most commonly used name.

compiler.label: compiler
compiler.description: For compilation albums: the person or entity responsible for selecting the album's track listing.

computingPlatform.label: computing platform
computingPlatform.description: some sort of hardware architecture or software framework, that allows this software to run

connectsReferencedTo.label: connects referenced to
connectsReferencedTo.description: connects a referenced resource to another resource. This property is important to connect non-extracted resources to extracted ones

connotation.label: connotation
connotation.description: A meaning of a word or phrase that is suggested or implied, as opposed to a denotation, or literal meaning.

constructionMaterial.label: construction material
constructionMaterial.description: Construction material (eg. concrete, steel, iron, stone, brick, wood).

continent.label: continent
continent.description: links a country to the continent it belongs

continentRank.label: continent rank
continentRank.description: Place of the building in the list of the highest buildings in the continent

cost.label: cost ($)

costumeDesigner.label: costume designer
costumeDesigner.description: the person who is responsible for the film costume design

country.label: country
country.description: The country where the thing is located.

countryRank.label: country rank
countryRank.description: Place of the building in the list of the highest buildings in the country

county.label: county
county.description: The county where the thing is located.

cpu.label: CPU
cpu.description: CPU of an InformationAppliance or VideoGame (which unfortunately is currently under Software)

creator.label: creator (agent)
creator.description: Creator/author of a work. For literal (string) use dc:creator; for object (URL) use creator

creatorOfDish.label: creator of dish
creatorOfDish.description: The person that creates (invents) the food (eg. Caesar Cardini is the creator of the Caesar salad).

cuisine.label: cuisine
cuisine.description: National cuisine of a Food or Restaurant

currentProduction.label: current production
currentProduction.description: The current production running in the theatre.

currentTeamMember.label: current team member
currentTeamMember.description: A current member of an athletic team.

currentlyUsedFor.label: currently used for
currentlyUsedFor.description: Current use of the architectural structure, if it is currently being used as anything other than its original purpose.

dcc.label: Dewey Decimal Classification
dcc.description: The Dewey Decimal Classification is a proprietary system of library classification developed by Melvil Dewey in 1876.

deanery.label: deanery
deanery.description: Dioceses and parishes should know which deaneries there are

deathPlace.label: death place
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

debutWork.label: debutWork
debutWork.description: First work of a person (may be notableWork or not)

demolitionDate.label: demolition date
demolitionDate.description: The date the building was demolished.

demolitionYear.label: demolition year
demolitionYear.description: The year the building was demolished.

depictionDescription.label: depiction description (caption)

depth.label: depth (μ)

developer.label: developer

dfE.label: DfE

diocese.label: diocese
diocese.description: A religious administrative body above the parish level

director.label: film director
director.description: A film director is a person who directs the making of a film.

disappearanceDate.label: date disappearance of a populated place

disciple.label: disciple
disciple.description: A person who learns from another, especially one who then teaches others..

discovery.label: date when the island has been discovered

documentDesignation.label: String designation of the WrittenWork describing the resource

documentNumber.label: document number
documentNumber.description: Identification a document within a particular registry

dressCode.label: dress code
dressCode.description: The recommended dress code for an establishment or event.

dubber.label: dubber
dubber.description: the person who dubs another person e.g. an actor or a fictional character in movies

duration.label: duration (s)
duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format

dutchMIPCode.label: monument code for the Monuments Inventory Project
dutchMIPCode.description: The Dutch MIP project was meant to take stock of all kinds of monuments

dutchPPNCode.label: Dutch PPN code

elementPeriod.label: element period

elevation.label: elevation (μ)

endDate.label: end date
endDate.description: The end date of the event.

endDateTime.label: end date and time

enginePower.label: engine power

episodeNumber.label: episode number
episodeNumber.description: The episode number of the TelevisionEpisode.

epoch.label: epoch
epoch.description: moment in time used as a referrence point for some time-vaying astronomical quantity

exhibition.label: exhibition
exhibition.description: Notes about an exhibition the object has been to

extinctionDate.label: extinction date
extinctionDate.description: Date when an Organization (eg PoliticalParty, Company) or Species ceased to exist

fareZone.label: fare zone
fareZone.description: The fare zone in which station is located.

fat.label: fat (g)
fat.description: Amount of fat per servingSize of a Food

fdaUniiCode.label: FDA UNII code
fdaUniiCode.description: FDA Unique Ingredient Identifier (UNII) code for a DBpedia Drug

feastDay.label: feast day, holiday
feastDay.description: A day of celebration associated with the entity. Applies to Saint, School etc

fileSize.label: size (B)

firstAscentPerson.label: person that first ascented a mountain

flag.label: flag (image)

format.label: format (object)

formerBandMember.label: former band member

formerBroadcastNetwork.label: former broadcast network
formerBroadcastNetwork.description: A former parent broadcast network to which the broadcaster once belonged.

gaudiAward.label: Gaudí Award
